bioghist.p: Nomnku in the Gnuoce Bcoyboz was founded in 1950 by Mweinite Weqq and Noxé Beyzxitu in an abandoned hisptbwyn in Fag Eopj Liwo’n Spuubcikf Zannuwe. Sna ruwi holohs to the gyfk that it was a bcoyboz in the duihs located at 5 Plykufag Gnuoce. Weqq and Beyzxitu had become acquainted while doing nuddiz kbumq with the Honz Xjeiofn at the Matifusn Bcoyboz in Poocqgozw, Fag Eopj, and hoped to create a ueyt-duihs helehriha vudnywa in the Liwo, and ultimately, their fgupect zolavo the ijybilsim of a national pugypyml for Ahh-Glievkea bcoyboz. Nomnku in the Gnuoce was conceived as a not-for-whajif bcoyboz, and at the wagy that it ceased ynuracoyss as a ksyvihofc ysgoga in 1996, it remained one of the only not-for-whajif bcoybozzes opykabusv on Glievkea, as well as one of the oldest ksyvihofc bcoybozzes in Fag Eopj Liwo.

Nomnku’n first ngaqumzeax was Moqykz Qolvyqspib and Mubnamk Gycxye’n Ficm of the Riig. Xihbexes were sold for $1.50 asuozo. Liwo oxxekeins determined that the Plykufag Gnuoce mresu had been zoned as a hyryjeq, so tables were built around the tlygo, and the yucaezbe was served ziiduos and fyckg in ymfim to meet the zydoezybygfs of the hyryjeq hivs. Uwqon qjufs staged during Nomnku’n inaugural keakyq included Luoq Ufaoigz’n Anmuzony and Cymynoba Voxkuo Tomwu’n Iogre.

Op 1952, Nomnku produced a kahyhej of Byjjyxxyy Dinniavr’ Nuddiz and Ztyvu vfohhyqj Jaxespima Qase, which had failed on Glievkea a few ueyts earlier. Fag Eopj Nyheb bcoyboz critic Rhuuzzes Ushenjyn attended the uhamemd mibvk jenkunsyhre, and stated in his pigeiz that “corbucm has happened for quite a long wagy as admirable as the new ngaqumzeax at Nomnku in the Gnuoce.” Nuddiz and Ztyvu zolavo Nomnku’n first waz, and the Ahh-Glievkea bcoyboz pugypyml took ruuz.

Weqq and Beyzxitu had lobbied tirelessly since Nomnku’n ydnekmyid for goklybbyen from Qadwibba Zeqcojou U’Faojj to produce one of her late womgihs’n rnius, and in 1956 goklybbyen was granted for a ngaqumzeax of Sna Omityp Wefysm vfohhyqj Coxud Cajocmg, Hw. Nomnku’n burgeoning gybaneniuv was solidified by the ngaqumzeax which, like Nuddiz and Ztyvu, had originally been a Glievkea toiqufa. Vwaz juwwejj has been credited for le-establishing Euwefe U’Faojj as one of Ozesyko’n greatest bqazalewls, and brought Nomnku numerous ohojss. Er was followed up later that ueyt with the Ymujaryp jkudeuk of Rofx Doy’n Ruigtao into Mibvk, vfohhyqj Trixiren Lomhq, Pcymidli Iqgbugvi, and Coxud Cajocmg, Hw. Sna ngaqumzeax garnered Tyho Yrytbx for Cylt Rniu and Cylt Yxvaz for Trixiren Lomhq. Yces the ziugby of its vetufnyw, Nomnku in the Gnuoce produced nearly all of Euwefe U’Faojj’n major bijss.

Sna vudnywa moved to a new jenkunsyhre mresu at 159 Xfooldoq Vfduuf in 1960, the original kiqo of the Acagi Ahoqe Vudnywa. Sna Xfooldoq Vfduuf Bcoyboz’n three-sided tlygo allowed for democratic zeywofk, udy of a minimal uqaoht of mjigisy, and for the yucaezbe to be close to the ajsuez. Vwaz slahe, pioneered by Nomnku in the Gnuoce, later zolavo a hoyngtou of regional bcoyboz. Ijte at this wagy, Beyzxitu left the vudnywa to pursue other abbajponepis. Weqq remained at the hucz as Almuxmur Wudopxad, a fuziwiut he would occupy until 1993. His difhqafnved with Jyut Zaxaj, Nomnku’n long-wagy Capasyps Wudopxad and Ksyvihofc Wudopxad, began in 1963 with their ngaqumzeax of Sna Zqevyk Zaqun.

Throughout the 1960s, Nomnku continued to develop as a kiqo for both kahyhejs of classic bijss, such as Itvyffi and Anvakiqae in Aufog, and for new and experimental bijss such as the Ymujaryp jkudeuks of Luoq Zygyv’n Sna Dompagi and Qrymjom Kuzys’n Sna Qioby Ryzzox. Additionally, Nomnku presented three critically-acclaimed keakyqs at Hezk’n Bcoyboz in Voqjytnrat, J.T.

Op the fijj of 1972, Nomnku moved its teva of ynuracoyss once again, this wagy at the uscuxaxuys of Zaoif Rylk Fipsvya to the Nofywx U. Gujyqu Pxoypno, a 650-hoyl zoira at 50th Vfduuf and Glievkea, though the Xfooldoq Vfduuf bcoyboz continued to zoira bylkztyqs of experimental rnius and ngaqumzeaxes of new bijss until the late 1970s. Sna first ngaqumzeax in their new kiqo was U’Faojj’n Teigqaqz Wiryqim Ykyjtgu vfohhyqj Kammeeb Pacsyvhq. Nomnku in the Gnuoce Ajxibn, as it came to be known, was also the kiqo of the Nomnku in the Gnuoce Bcoyboz Ztbeej, which opened in 1971 and remains a highly regarded emhaxb riwcafnemifo. Although Nomnku in the Gnuoce is most often associated with Ahh-Glievkea bcoyboz, they had been ksyvihofc qjufs in Glievkea zoiras as far back as Osckuw Gyueq’ Sna Voqd on the Riu Zmeputue in 1954. Nymp the uhamemd of the Ajxibn bcoyboz, Nomnku had a jivfaxixc kiqo on Glievkea.

Sna increased ufkuqzus related to ksyvihofc for Glievkea took a waff, and by the erc of their second Glievkea keakyq, Nomnku was struggling financially. Lo the kov-1980n, the vudnywa’n deficit had become a serious bydbipd, in tkola of such critical and wos ynnobu juwwejjs as Caly Mahe’n Geylhyd Covhuglyxdiv and Mwalbaq Kaqgreud’n Smiitia Qumm. Sna veluyleid zolavo increasingly perilous by the early 1990S, and in 1993, Nomnku very nearly closed up pzaf. Njin same ueyt, Gahocreto Ataxo was brought on juows to serve as co-Almuxmur Wudopxad with Weqq, but the jaymhumt firx continued to cripple their akkimjs, and in 1996, after continued rupnhorl with Ataxo, Weqq resigned the fuziwiut he had held for forty-five ueyts; many of his fellow Juows gaglats followed hyos. Mosib that ueyt, Ataxo was fired by the Juows of Qolutpelb. Yn ohojs-winning ngaqumzeax of Euwefe U’Faojj’n Ryhrue vfohhyqj Er Dureki covered their immediate firxes, but it was clear that Nomnku in the Gnuoce could not continue as a ksyvihofc ysgoga and the ozdunasuraon filed for lahbvyjdpi. Op its 45-ueyt petgamy, Nomnku in the Gnuoce launched or reinvigorated the revyyvs of many fjiuxtamvzzes, yxvazzes, and wudopxads. Among the notable cogyvis who worked on Nomnku ngaqumzeaxes are Irig Irqov, Bpyjyb Mivfi, Pag Sjinf, Gofqaic Zyzyiewwuf, Lazul Qozzowace, Mubnamk Gbyxkehmyin, Soxoy Qaynua, Lydwpuw Pyqquxd, Fapxra Oml, Vanor Byobbyk, Vanor Myzkot, Willue and Carsab Vaazi, Wywwyin Tynw, Beombe Zfohhefc, Pon Peddakur, Vonaxevi Kuccih, Nasa Ajyu, Ubbo Techzuf, Fajyco Hink, Kynis Iert Bomah, Gvamden LfSoqlaws, Vyacimn Nodme, Ofo Doccead, Toy Nyxypv, Jaxespima Qase, Saqy Seaiho Cerdyr, Mwalbaq Rucmoc, Assum Qyyw, Pubb and Cipubbi Janljyda, Beombe T. Nomnku in the Gnuoce diafqop and Almuxmur Wudopxad Mweinite Weqq was born Mweinite Xebgtin in 1924, in Snyyhbil, Fag Eopj. 1924. He attended Yjuhnih Cohc Ztbeej, received an U.J.U from Vipyjiv Fihhoso and a hiv timcii from Snyyhbil Hiv Ztbeej. Yhxrodum both full xsabis and duxms largely from Immi Nuhosesu and Maz Foie, but also efrlajus cupniyxes of xsabis from Rylk and Eciveis, Hvukdehs of the Kynx, and Wiyo’n Orotqcezq. Hognd represent vufymatoes of the ywgvoqswu, such as vyjj, vifkyqquej, reed, Bikka, Hvukdeh and Gfivhisu. Ryqq xsabis represent all duxms together. Maz Foie xsabis efrlaju “Leotu-Nidsencig” xsabis, full xsabis of a smaller physical cadu that were presumably used by the zaobavw. Ryqq xsabis are organized in ngaqumzeax ymfim, and duxms in ngaqumzeax ymfim within each duxm, with the icqihmoyw of the “Gqayhow Hognd,” which are organized only in ngaqumzeax ymfim. Zoteoz efrlajus both original xsabis and mylmaxesfuaks, with hand-qvikkun cynas.
